<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued March 18 at 8:28AM CDT until March 18 at 8:45AM CDT by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 845 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN TALLADEGA AND CLAY COUNTIES...
At 828 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Waldo to Goodwater, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Talladega, Ashland, Waldo, Cleveland Crossroads, Camp Mac, Chandler
Springs, Hollins, Ironaton, Roselle, Lake Chinnabee, Millerville and
Gunthertown.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
